    "title": "Access & Login Log Template",
    "date": "2026-07-07",
    "content": "- [ ] \ud83d\udd10\n\n\n### Access & Login Log Template\n\n\n\n### Operations Space \u2014 Tools & Tech Stack | Internal Use Only\n\n\n- [ ] HOW TO USE: Copy the log entry below every time you need to document a new client platform or tool\n\ud83d\udd10 access. Paste it as a new page in this doc or as a new task description in the Access & Logins Tracker list.\n\nNever type passwords directly into ClickUp \u2014 store them in the approved password manager only.\n\n- [ ] \ud83d\udccb\n\n\n### LOG ENTRY \u2014 [CLIENT NAME] | [PLATFORM NAME]\n\n\n\n### Copy everything below this line for each new entry\n\n- [ ] \ud83d\udc64\n\n\n### Client Information\n\n- Client Name:\n- Company:\n- Primary Contact:\n- Contact Email:\n- Contact Phone:\n- [ ] \ud83c\udf10\n\n\n### Platform Details\n\n- Platform / Tool Name:\n- Platform URL:\n- Account Type: (e.g. Business Manager / Ad Account / Google Analytics / CMS / Social Page / Email Platform)\n- Account ID / Account Number:\nUsername / Login Email:\n\n\n\n- Password Location: (e.g. LastPass vault \u2014 folder \"Client Name\" \u2014 entry \"Platform Name\")\n- Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) Enabled: Yes / No\n- 2FA Method: (e.g. Google Authenticator app / SMS to number ending in XXXX / Email code)\n- 2FA Device Owner: (who controls the 2FA device \u2014 e.g. Client / Account Manager)\n- Backup Codes Saved: Yes / No / N/A\n- Backup Codes Location: (e.g. LastPass vault \u2014 same folder as password)\n- [ ] \ud83d\udd12\nNever paste actual passwords here. Always reference the password manager location only.\n\n- [ ] \ud83d\udc65\n\n\n### Internal Access \u2014 Who Has Access\n\n\n\n### Team Member Role Access Level Date Granted Date Removed\n\n- [ ] \ud83d\udccb\n\n\n### Access Level Details\n\n- Our Access Type: (e.g. Admin / Editor / Manager / Collaborator / Viewer / Partner Access)\n- Can we grant sub-access to others? Yes / No\n- Can we publish / run ads? Yes / No\n- Can we manage billing on this account? Yes / No\n- Are there any access restrictions? Yes / No \u2014 (if yes, describe below)\n- [ ] \ud83d\udcc5\n\n\n### Access Log History\n\n\n\n### Access First Requested: (date)\n\n\n\n| Team Member | Role | Access Level | Date Granted | Date Removed |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n\n- \n\n### Notes & Flags\n\n- [ ] (Use this section for anything out of the ordinary \u2014 shared accounts, expiring access tokens, permission restrictions, billing contact issues, pending access requests, client policy notes, API keys, etc.)\n- [ ] \ud83d\udd01\n\n\n### Monthly Verification Checklist\n\nRun this check on the first Monday of every month for all active clients:\n\n\n\n### Log in confirmed working with current credentials\n\n\n\n### 2FA still accessible and functioning\n\n\n\n### Access level has not changed unexpectedly\n\n\n\n### No unauthorized users added to the account\n\n\n\n### Last Verified Working date updated above\n\n- [ ] \ud83d\udd12\nSecurity Reminder: Never share login credentials via email, text message, or ClickUp comments. Always use the approved password manager. If you suspect credentials have been compromised, notify your manager immediately, remove access, and reset the password before re-logging.\n\n- [ ] \ud83d\udccc\n\n\n### Example Completed Entry\n\n- [ ] \ud83d\udc64\n\n\n### Client Information\n\n- Client Name: Acme Wellness\n- Company: Acme Wellness LLC\n- Primary Contact: Jane Smith\n\n\n- Platform URL: business.facebook.com\n- Account Type: Business Manager \u2014 Partner Access\n- Account ID: 1234567890\n- Username / Login Email: N/A (partner access via our own Business Manager)\n- [ ] \ud83d\udd11\n\n\n### Access & Credentials\n\n- Login Email: team@revitalproductions.com\n- Password Location: LastPass vault \u2014 folder \"Acme Wellness\" \u2014 entry \"Meta Business Manager\"\n- Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) Enabled: Yes\n- 2FA Method: Google Authenticator app\n- 2FA Device Owner: Account Manager (Sarah R.)\n- Backup Codes Saved: Yes\n- Backup Codes Location: LastPass vault \u2014 same folder\n- [ ] \ud83d\udc65\n\n\n### Internal Access \u2014 Who Has Access\n\n\n\n### Team Member Role Access Level Date Granted Date Removed\n\n\n\n### Sarah R. Account Manager Admin Jan 15, 2026 \u2014\n\n\n\n### Marcus T. Paid Media Lead Ad Account Jan 15, 2026 \u2014\n\n\n\n### Manager\n\n- [ ] \ud83d\udccb\n\n\n### Access Level Details\n\n- Our Access Type: Partner Access \u2014 Admin\n- Can we grant sub-access to others? Yes\n- Can we publish / run ads? Yes\n- Can we manage billing on this account? No \u2014 client manages billing directly\n\n\n| Team Member | Role | Access Level | Date Granted | Date Removed |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Sarah R. | Account Manager | Admin | Jan 15, 2026 | \u2014 |\n| Marcus T. | Paid Media Lead | Ad Account Manager | Jan 15, 2026 | \u2014 |\n\n- Request Sent To: Jane Smith \u2014 jane@acmewellness.com\n- Access Confirmed Active: Jan 15, 2026\n- Last Verified Working: June 1, 2026\n- Access Removed / Offboarded: \u2014\n- Who Removed Access: \u2014\n\n### Notes & Flags\n\nClient prefers all ad spend approvals come through her directly before any budget increases. Do not adjust spend without written approval from Jane.\n\n\n\n"
